<h2>Wyndelle's Misadventures Part Three</h2>
<div class="tale">
	<h5>By: Wyndelle</h5>
	<div class="text">
		Wyndelle's Misadventures Part Three<br />
By Wyndelle<br />
<br />
"Mmmmththmm gbgbbmmmtg" said Gebarn. A dust covered gnome looked up from the small piles of dirt and debris that he was trying to coerce into bigger piles. "What?!?" he asked the elemental. "Sooo mtrewqhd arekl;jn for" Gebarn said through mounds of mushy food.<br />
<br />
"It's pointless to try to talk to me until you've finished eating Gebarn, though I guess you don't have a mother to teach ya proper manners" sighed Wyndelle. <br />
<br />
With the food that Wyndelle had summoned, Gebarn was now approaching normal size. With a grunt, he swallowed the remainder of the food, then proceeded to loudly belch a small cloud of noxious fumes that smelled of burnt bread. "I said, so what are ya in for... whatcha do? Steal a scroll?" asked the elemental.<br />
<br />
"Honestly I have no idea" replied Wyndelle. "My brothers and I were traveling to Freeport, and I woke up with the old man yelling at me." sighed the young gnome. "All I want to do is rejoin my brothers. We are searching for answers to an ancient prophecy" explained Wyndelle.<br />
<br />
Gebarn burped another cloud and moved away from the table. From above the old gnome shouted down to Gebarn "If you've eaten get yer arse up here!" Gebarn looked at Wyndelle, shrugged his shoulders, and floated up the stairs.<br />
<br />
As Wyndelle completed the tasks assigned to him, bits and pieces of an argument would occasionally float down the stairs. "No.... he ....master orders."<br />
<br />
Wyndelle finally got the library dusted and cleaned and crossed the room to begin work on the lab. As he opened the door his nose was assaulted by various smells. Apparently not only was the old gnome forgetful he was a slob. Stained beakers were scattered about, 200-year-old mummified apple cores, and some things that seemed to have taken a life of their own were scattered about the lab.<br />
<br />
Tired, hot and weary from previous exertions, Wyndelle dusted a stool off and sat. Just then Gebarn floated into the room, a scowl on his face and 2 pieces of parchment in his hands. He threw them down on the table in front of Wyndelle, then floated to a corner of the room to sulk.<br />
<br />
Wyndelle picked the parchments up, and asked Gebarn "What are these?..." Gebarn was silent for a moment, sighed then responded. "The first is a list of references and tomes that the old man wants you to retrieve from the library." explained Gebarn. "And the second?" asked Wyndelle..." I can't read it.... It's all gibberish" said Wyndelle.<br />
<br />
Gebarn sighed looked at Wyndelle, then replied. "Apparently the old man thinks that it best that I belong to you. He no longer has the time to devote to me, and he thinks that you and I will better serve each other. The second parchment is the transfer of ownership."<br />
<br />
A small grin developed on Wyndelle's face, then a smile. "You mean...You have to call me..." "NEVER!" interrupted Gebarn. "I will sooner call you master, than Elves start flyin" huffed Gebarn.<br />
<br />
Just then a scratching was heard at the window. Wyndelle moved closer, his eyes widened then brightened as he smiled, for there was his friend Perth bobbing in the air just outside the window....... 60 feet above the ground.<br />
<br />
"Arrr Maties!!" greeted Perth. He looked around at the mess that used to be a lab, then back at Wyndelle. "You wouldn't happen to know if there's any honeycomb in there would ye?" Wyndelle slowly turned to Gebarn.<br />
<br />
Gebarn gave a resigned sigh and began to sift through the debris..."I know I know.... I am looking MASTER."<br />
<br />
"Gebarn can find ye what ye need, I have some looking to do myself, I'll be in the library when yer through" said Wyndelle. He walked into the library, looking at row after row of spell books and research materials. He looked at the list and started his search with a sigh.
	</div>
